<TITLE> FFs injured, awarded to get VIP status </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 19 (bdnews24.com)All freedom fighters (FFs) having gallantry awards and injured in the war of independence will get VIP status soon, liberation war affairs ministry officials told a parliamentary panel on Tuesday. State minister for liberation war affairs minister Tajul Islam told bdnews24.com that his ministry had sent a summary on the proposal for the prime minister's approval. If approved, 5027 injured freedom fighters and 676 freedom fighters winning four gallantry awardsBir Sreshthha, Bir Uttam, Bir Bikram and Bir Protikwill get special treatment in the government entities and invitation at all state programmes. The parliamentary standing committee on the planning ministry at its Tuesday's meeting said it would recommend the government to recoginse all 1.5 lakh living freedom fighters as VIPs. "A few days ago, we sent a summary to the prime minister's office for the approval of a proposal to give the injured and award winning freedom fighters VIP treatments," Islam, who did not attend the meeting, told bdnews24.com. "I think it would be endorsed as the prime minister has a very soft corner for the freedom fighters," he said. Seven freedom fighters have got highest gallantry award Bir Shreshthha, followed by 68 Bir Uttam, 175 Bir Bikram and 426 Bir Protik, according to the ministry. "We want that all freedom fighters should get VIP treatment. We could not honour them (before), we have to start now," Oli Ahmad, Bir Bikram, the committee chairman, told bdnews24.com. The state minister in principle agreed with the chairman, but said the move would face some practical problems. "There are many freedom fighters who don't have even a lungi (to wear) to come out. So, we have to think about it. "We want to do something for them," said Islam.
